=== Higashiagatsuma Town Designated Important Cultural Properties ===
* Carvings and {{ill|lt=mikoshi|Q979940|qid=Q979940|lt=portable shrine|1=Mikoshi}} of Kawasukune Shrine (designated March 23, Shōwa 48)<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |title=List of Town-Designated Cultural Properties |url=https://www.town.higashiagatsuma.gunma.jp/www/contents/1447054044287/index.html |website=Higashiagatsuma Town, Gunma Prefecture |access-date=2024-08-21 |language=ja}}</ref> – The mikoshi is said to date from {{ill|lt=Tenshō|Q1145058|qid=Q1145058|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)}} 3 ({{ill|lt=1575|Q6688|qid=Q6688|1=1575}}){{Sfn|Azuma Village History Compilation Committee|1965|pp=674–676}}.

=== Higashiagatsuma Town Designated Natural Monuments ===
* Large {{ill|lt=zelkova|Q920344|qid=Q920344|lt=keyaki|1=Zelkova serrata}} tree of Kawasukune Shrine (designated March 23, Shōwa 48)<ref name=":0" /> – Said to be over 700 years old; there are five other zelkova trees of similar age within the precincts{{Sfn|Azuma Village History Compilation Committee|1965|p=891}}.

